<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 27 at 1:22AM CDT  by NWS Amarillo</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northwestern
Randall, southeastern Oldham and southwestern Potter Counties through
145 AM CDT...
At 122 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles northwest of Bushland, or 16 miles west of Amarillo, moving
east at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Amarillo and Bushland.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
